        <h1 style="font-size:6vw">Different types of Hamster Breeds</h1>
         <h2 style="font-size:4vw"><em>Syrian Hamster</em></h2>
	      <img src="images/images/syrianham.jpeg" alt="Grey Syrian Hamster" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
          <p style="font-size:2vw">Traits: unsociable, calm, nocturnal,likes to be alone </p>
          <p style="font-size:2vw">Average lifespan: 2-3 years</p>
	      <p style="font-size:2vw">Average size: around 3-4 inches</p>
       
         <h2 style="font-size:4vw"><em>Chinese Hamster</em></h2>
	      <img src="images/images/chinesehamster.jpg" alt="Chinese Hamster" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
          <p style="font-size:2vw">Traits: quick,playful,high maintenance,hyperactive</p>
	      <p style="font-size:2vw">Average lifespan: 2-3 years</p>
	      <p style="font-size:2vw">Average size: 3-4 inches 
	  
	     <h2 style="font-size:4vw"><em>Roborovski Hamster</em></h2>
	       <img src="images/images/roboham.jpg" alt="A tiny Robo Hamster" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
	       <p style="font-size:2vw">Traits: sociable, fast, selfish, independent, like to live with other hamsters 
	       <p style="font-size:2vw">Average lifespan:2.5-3 years 
	       <p style="font-size:2vw">Average size: 2 inches </p>
	     
	     <h2 style="font-size:4vw"><em>Cambell Russian Hamster</em></h2>
	      <img src="images/images/campbellham.jpg" alt="A Dark Grey Campbell" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;">
	      <p style="font-size:2vw"> Traits: shy, affectionate, likes extremely quiet places, like hiding </p>
	      <p style="font-size:2vw">Average lifespan: 1.5-2 years </p>
	      <p style="font-size:2vw">Average size: 2-4 years </p>
	    
	     <h2 style="font-size:4vw">Hamster housing</h2>
	       <ul>
	        <li style="font-size:2vw">All species of hamsters like big and spacious environment. Wired cages are bad. A big plastic container is better.</li>
	         <li style="font-size:2vw">Containers should be atleast 24 inches by 12 inches. </li>
	          <li style="font-size:2vw">Lots of places to hide is recommended. With fresh food and water daily.</li>
	          <li style="font-size:2vw">Quiet and secluded spaces are ideal to place cages </li>
	           </ul>
	   
